**Nerve : A nerve is the bundle of fibre that carries signal between diffrent part of body and brain enabling sensation and movement and othe nody function:
Neuron:
i)it  is structural and functionl unit of nervous syetm
ii)longest cell in the body:
iii)carry message in the form of electrical impulse and signal:
 dendrites: it collects information:
 Axon: electrical impulse travel along axon:
Mylean sheath:prevents leaking out of signals from axons:
cell body : it takes the information from the dendrites in form electrical signal:
nerve ending: electrical impulse cause relaese of signal:

**Synapse:
i)Microscopic gap between two nuerons:
ii)the role of synapse is to transfer the electric impulse from one neuron to another. at a synapse the electrical impulse cause the relaese of chemical from the nerve dening of one neuron. these chemicals cross the synaptic gap and reaches dendrites tip
  of next neuron generating a new electrical signal in that neuron:

** transmission of impulse between two neurons:
chemical collected at the end of dendritic tip:
